@node COPYRIGHT "ABC-Patterns.guide/COPYRIGHT NOTE"

   COPYRIGHT NOTE:
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   ABC-PATTERNS is Mailware and absolutely FREE distributable!

   You are allowed to re-distribute this package as long as you follow
   these points:

   1. Any Re-Distribution has to include @{"all files" link CONTENTS} in this archive,
      including this document file, without any modifications!

   2. This package may be freely distributed via BBSs, InterNet/UseNet,
      software libraries such as Fred Fish's and Aminet CD-ROM, and other
      similar electronic channels.
      Disk magazines and services that charge extra for file transfers may
      NOT distribute ABC-PATTERNS.

   You are allowed to convert your favourite patterns for a non-proportional
   screenmode (640x256, for example) if you can`t use the flickering modes
   on your monitor, but please don`t include them into the package.

   You are NOT allowed to use ABC-PATTERNS or any part of it for any other
   purpose than that one mentioned above, this also includes the images the
   patterns consist of.

   By using these patterns, you accept the full responsibility for any
   damage or loss that may occur through their use. The author can not be
   held responsible. (I hope this is a less important point.)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 NONE of the patterns may be used on any machine which is used for research,
 development, construction, testing or production of weapons or other
 military applications. This includes any machine used for training persons
 for any of the above mentioned purposes.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

